@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Email Notification Settings";
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 offset-md-2">
            <div class="card shadow">
                <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                    <h2>@ViewData["Title"]</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h4 class="mb-4">Email Notification for Unauthorized Access</h4>
                    
                    <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <p>NueroDrive can send email notifications when an unauthorized person attempts to access your vehicle.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h5 class="mt-4">How Email Notifications Work</h5>
                    <p>When the facial recognition system detects an unauthorized person attempting to access your vehicle, an email alert will be sent to the vehicle owner's email address with details about:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The vehicle that was accessed</li>
                        <li>The time of the access attempt</li>
                        <li>Instructions for contacting support if needed</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h5 class="mt-4">Email Configuration</h5>
                    <p>To enable email notifications, you need to configure the system with valid SMTP server settings in the <code>appsettings.json</code> file:</p>
                    
                    <pre class="bg-light p-3 mb-4"><code>{
  "EmailSettings": {
    "SmtpHost": "smtp.gmail.com",
    "SmtpPort": "587",
    "SmtpUsername": "your-email@gmail.com",
    "SmtpPassword": "your-app-password",
    "SenderEmail": "your-email@gmail.com"
  }
}</code></pre>
                    
                    <h5 class="mt-4">Using Gmail for Notifications</h5>
                    <p>If you're using Gmail, you'll need to:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Enable 2-Step Verification on your Google account</li>
                        <li>Generate an App Password (16-character code)</li>
                        <li>Use this App Password in your configuration instead of your regular password</li>
                    </ol>
                    
                    <div class="alert alert-warning">
                        <strong>Note:</strong> Never share your email credentials or include them in public repositories or shared code.
                    </div>
                    
                    <h5 class="mt-4">Testing Email Notifications</h5>
                    <p>After configuring your email settings, you can test the notification system by:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Making an API call to any of the face verification endpoints with an unrecognized face</li>
                        <li>Checking your email for the notification</li>
                        <li>Reviewing application logs for any email sending errors</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div> 